PAGE.PY - to add simple xwiki page
----------------------------------

usage: page.py [-h] [--url [URL]] [--username [USERNAME]]
               [--password [PASSWORD]] [--parent [PARENT]] [--title [TITLE]]
               [--wiki [WIKI]] [--content [CONTENT]]
               [--attachments [ATTACHMENTS [ATTACHMENTS ...]]]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --url [URL], -U [URL]
                        base url of your xwiki, http://192.168.0.1:8080/xwiki
                        e.g.; you also can use XWIKI_URL system variable to
                        specify
  --username [USERNAME], -u [USERNAME]
                        XWIKI username, system variable - XWIKI_USER
  --password [PASSWORD], -p [PASSWORD]
                        XWIKI password, system variable XWIKI_PWD
  --parent [PARENT], -P [PARENT]
                        point separated path to your page home, XWiki.New
                        Pages e.g.
  --title [TITLE], -c [TITLE]
                        your page title
  --wiki [WIKI], -W [WIKI]
                        if you use non-default wiki home you can specify
                        other, default : xwiki
  --content [CONTENT], -C [CONTENT]
                        file with your page content, will be readed from STDIN
                        if not specified
  --attachments [ATTACHMENTS [ATTACHMENTS ...]], -a [ATTACHMENTS [ATTACHMENTS ...]]
                        files will be attached to your page
